<StaticPageLayout
  title="Affiliate disclosure"
  description="How commercial links work, what they can fund, and what they can never buy at evidique."
  kicker="The money note"
>
  <p>
    <strong>Effective July 11, 2026.</strong> Commercial relationships are disclosed where they appear.
  </p>
  <h2>What an affiliate link does</h2><p>
    If you follow a labeled affiliate link and buy something, the site may receive a commission. The
    price you pay should not increase because of that referral.
  </p>
  <h2>What it cannot do</h2><p>
    Affiliate availability does not qualify a product for coverage, improve a score, create a
    category win, or suppress a limitation.
  </p>
  <h2>Technical labeling</h2><p>
    Sponsored commercial links open in a new tab and use <code
      >nofollow sponsored noopener noreferrer</code
    >. The link data lives in one central file so editors can disable it without hunting through
    articles.
  </p>
</StaticPageLayout>
